"Based on the retrieved social media posts, the following facts and claims regarding Ferguson are summarized using the three-state evidence model:\n\n**Verified-Fact**\n*   **Media Sensitivity and Terminology:** There is significant sensitivity among people in Ferguson regarding media descriptions of \"rioting.\" A verified user notes that behavior accurately described as rioting occurred only on Sunday, implying that other days or events may have been mischaracterized by media outlets [4].\n\n**Informal-but-Genuine**\n*   **Solidarity and Context:** Verified users express solidarity with Ferguson [3]. An unverified user contextualizes the event by noting parallel incidents, specifically mentioning another killing of a black man by police in Los Angeles that received less media attention [5].\n\n**Unverified-Rumour**\n*   **Police Jamming Livestreams:** A claim that police are using jammers to take down livestreams in Ferguson is present but remains unverified due to being a single-source report with no mutual corroboration [1].\n*   **Police Report Availability:** A post claims to provide a \"full\" police report on Mike Brown; however, this is treated as unverified due to the unverified status of the source and low claim support metrics [2]."